<clause id="_what_is_measured" obligation="normative" displayorder="5">
<title depth="1">5.<tab/>What is Measured?</title>
<ul id="_6fa67e68-96cb-7ff5-2ea4-f9e6f7fa9a61"><li><p id="_4c8fe7c3-1688-6e73-07a8-332b9e2e9402"><strong>Number of Subscribers</strong><br/>
The number of specific subscribers on a network. Each subscriber may represent more than
one end-user or include multiple devices.</p>
</li>
<li><p id="_eb333063-a08d-c0f6-6a21-3171cedb0907"><strong>Infected Subscribers</strong><br/>
This is the count of unique subscribers identified to be infected in each reporting period.</p>
</li>
<li><p id="_4ae7782b-e4ac-409e-58c9-e7319e29e6d4"><strong>Percent of Base Infected</strong><br/>
Calculated from above: Infected Subscribers divided by Number of Subscribers</p>
</li>
<li><p id="_114bc3d2-0799-1e6f-c6d0-9db9ce40d7c3"><strong>Total Number of Infected Subscribers Notified</strong><br/>
The number of unique subscribers notified of a bot by any method, including text message,
phone call, email, Web redirection or browser notification, and postal mail. Multiple notices
sent to the same subscriber are counted as one. This does not imply that the subscriber
received or read the notice.</p>
</li>
<li><p id="_b3346e56-ab4f-3961-9e75-01b88f74ccb9"><strong>Percent Notified</strong><br/>
Calculated from above: Infected Subscribers Notified / Infected Subscribers</p>
</li>
</ul>
</clause>
